@page "/software-development"

<PageTitle>Product Development – Xipe</PageTitle>

<!-- HERO -->
<section id="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="hero-photo" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555066931-4365d14bab8c?w=1920&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80'); opacity: 0.3;"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-badge">Product Development</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">
            Ship faster.<br />
            Build right.<br />
            <em>Launch with confidence.</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
            Your product runs on an AI-augmented development pipeline that tests, validates, and ships code from day one; not at the end.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-subtitle-2">
            No surprises. No wasted sprints. Just working software, delivered continuously.
        </p>
        <a href="/#contact" class="btn-hero">Build your product with us &rarr;</a>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FLIP THE SCRIPT -->
<section id="flip">
    <div class="inner">
        <div class="flip-grid">
            <div class="flip-problem">
                <p>Traditional teams spend months writing code before validating a single assumption.</p>
                <p class="risky">That's expensive. And it's avoidable.</p>
                <div class="flip-script">We flip the script.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flip-diana">
                <span class="label">Powered by DIANA</span>
                <p>
                    <a href="https://metaprogramming.ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>DIANA</strong></a> defines exactly how every feature should behave before a single line is written. Each piece of functionality is verified the moment it exists; not in a final QA sprint weeks later.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Your product, architecture, and decisions are documented automatically as development progresses. Your team moves fast; without losing clarity or control.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flip-proof">
            <p>One source of truth. Zero guesswork.</p>
            <strong>We prove it works; from day one.</strong>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- WHAT YOU GET -->
<section id="what-you-get">
    <div class="inner">
        <div class="wyg-header">
            <span class="wyg-label">What You Get</span>
            <h2 class="wyg-title">A Minimal Commercial Product</h2>
            <p class="wyg-intro">The <strong>first real version of your product</strong>; not a prototype, not a demo.</p>
            <p class="wyg-intro-2">Your MCP is built to operate your business, serve real users, and validate your market from day one. Production-ready. Commercially viable. Immediately.</p>
            <p class="wyg-foundation">Built to scale. Not to be rewritten.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="wyg-grid">
            <div class="wyg-card">
                <h3><i class="bi bi-box-seam"></i> Your product includes</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>A production-ready .NET platform engineered for your market</li>
                    <li>The core features needed to deliver your service through the product</li>
                    <li>A scalable architecture that evolves with real usage; not assumptions</li>
                    <li>Clean foundations that eliminate costly rewrites down the road</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="wyg-card">
                <h3><i class="bi bi-stars"></i> What that means for you</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Faster time to market; without sacrificing quality</li>
                    <li>Full code ownership. No vendor lock-in, ever</li>
                    <li>Visible progress every sprint; measurable, not just promised</li>
                    <li>Real user feedback integrated from the first release</li>
                    <li>A roadmap that flexes without derailing your timeline</li>
                    <li>A technical foundation that supports growth, not just launch</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="wyg-cta">
            <a href="/#contact" class="btn-wyg">Let's scope your project &rarr;</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW WE WORK -->
<section id="how-we-work" style="padding: 120px 64px;">
    <div class="inner" style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="hww-header">
            <span class="hww-label">How We Work</span>
            <h2 class="hww-title">Structured for speed. Engineered to last.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="hww-phases">
            <div class="phase-card">
                <span class="phase-tag">Phase 01</span>
                <div class="phase-timeline">Weeks 1–4</div>
                <h3>Blueprint</h3>
                <p>
                    We align on your idea, your market, and your business goals. The output is a clear product blueprint; what gets built, why it matters, and how it evolves. Every future decision traces back to this foundation.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="phase-card">
                <span class="phase-tag">Phase 02</span>
                <div class="phase-timeline">Weeks 1–4</div>
                <h3>Pipeline</h3>
                <p>
                    In parallel, we deploy the DIANA-powered development pipeline. This becomes the operating engine behind every sprint; continuous validation, automated testing, and delivery without the bottlenecks.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="phase-card">
                <span class="phase-tag">Phase 03</span>
                <div class="phase-timeline">Months 2–6</div>
                <h3>Flow</h3>
                <p>
                    Development begins. Real progress, every week. Features prioritized by business impact; not by arbitrary backlog order. Continuous delivery, continuous feedback, continuous momentum.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- GREENFIELD -->
<section id="greenfield">
    <div class="inner">
        <div>
            <span class="gf-label">Built for New Products</span>
            <h2 class="gf-title">We specialize in <em>greenfield.</em><br />Zero legacy. Zero compromise.</h2>
            <p class="gf-body">We don't patch broken systems or inherit other teams' technical debt. We build from a clean slate; so the architecture serves your product, not someone else's past decisions.</p>
            <ul class="gf-list">
                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i> Clean architecture engineered from day one</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i> No legacy code to untangle or work around</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i> No inherited debt slowing your roadmap</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i> Built to evolve with your business; not replaced by it</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="gf-callout">
            <p>You bring the vision.</p>
            <strong>We bring the engineering system to build it right; the first time.</strong>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FINAL CTA -->
<section id="final-cta">
    <div class="cta-glow"></div>
    <div class="inner">
        <span class="cta-label">Next Step</span>
        <h2 class="cta-title">Let's build<br /><em>your product.</em></h2>
        <p class="cta-body">
            Share your vision. We'll design the path to get there; with a clear plan tailored to your goals, timeline, and market.
        </p>
        <a href="/#contact" class="btn-hero">Send us your idea &rarr;</a>
    </div>
</section>
